{"type":"message","id":"3f097a0a","parentId":"1ed1f467","timestamp":"2026-02-11T01:29:02.668Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron job was never set up in the system crontab. According to the config, it should run at 23:00 UTC (7:00 AM SGT). Let me set up the cron job using OpenClaw's cron tool, which is the proper way to do it.\n\nFor the daily ping, I need to:\n1. Create a cron job that runs the daily-ping-cron.sh script\n2. The script collects data and writes to a log file\n3. Then the message needs to be delivered to Telegram\n\nLooking at the cron tool docs, I can create a job with:\n- sessionTarget: \"main\" or \"isolated\"\n- payload.kind: \"systemEvent\" or \"agentTurn\"\n- schedule.kind: \"cron\"\n\nBut wait - the daily-ping-cron.sh script already does the data collection and writes to a log. What I need is:\n1. Either run that script via system cron\n2. Or create an OpenClaw cron job that does the whole thing\n\nLet me create an OpenClaw cron job that triggers the agent to send the daily ping. The schedule should be `0 23 * * *` (11pm UTC = 7am SGT).\n\nActually, looking at the config more carefully, it says:\n- Method: HEARTBEAT.md trigger (not direct cron)\n- Timing: ~7:05 AM SGT (after data collection)\n- Process: Heartbeat checks log file → Formats message → Sends via Telegram\n\nSo the design was:\n1. System cron runs the shell script at 23:00 UTC (7am SGT)\n2. Script collects data and writes to log\n3. Heartbeat picks up the log and sends message\n\nBut the system cron isn't set up. Let me fix this by:\n1. Adding the system cron job to run the script\n2. Also creating an OpenClaw cron job as backup that sends the message directly\n\nLet me set up both - the shell script via system cron AND an OpenClaw agentTurn job that can do the full workflow.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The system crontab was never set up. Let me fix this two ways:\n\n1. **Add system cron** to run the data collection script\n2. **Create OpenClaw cron job** as a backup that sends the message directly"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"877707f9-8fc4-4fb8-a75d-e9892b757cc1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Add the daily ping to system crontab\n(crontab -l 2>/dev/null; echo \"# Daily ping at 7am SGT (23:00 UTC)\"; echo \"0 23 * * * /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh >> /home/project/openclaw/logs/cron.log 2>&1\") | crontab - && echo \"Crontab installed:\" && crontab -l"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/pony-alpha","usage":{"input":1657,"output":1015,"cacheRead":51648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54320,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770773274083}}
